hopobject.body: We used to work together anastrozole drugs.com The willingness of some launch officers to leave the blast door open at times reflects a mindset far removed from the Cold War days when the U.S. lived in fear of a nuclear strike by the Soviet Union. It was that fear that provided the original rationale for placing ICBMs in reinforced underground silos and the launch control officers in buried capsules -- so that in the event of an attack the officers might survive to launch a counterattack.
